hiru to her) than a genuine crush though.</li><li> Rima and Shiki.</li><li> Yuuki and Aidou.</li><li> For three episodes of the anime, the intro included a quick shot of Ruka leaning in to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss">Almost Kiss</a> Yuuki.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowDontTell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowDontTell">Show, Don't Tell</a>: Usually the case with Zero/Yuuki moments.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork">Shown Their Work</a>: When it comes to weapons, Hino Matsuri purchased a book about them to make the ones in the story look as realistic as possible. For example, Zero's gun is a Desert Eagle. <a class="urllink" href="http://images.wikia.com/stateofdecay/images/c/c4/448914-desert_eagle.jpg">[1]<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a><small>&loz;</small></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shoujo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Shoujo">Shoujo</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowerOfAngst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShowerOfAngst">Shower of Angst</a>: Zero in the anime. Though it's only for a few quick seconds.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SickeninglySweethearts" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SickeninglySweethearts">Sickeningly Sweethearts</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyMarried" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyMarried">Haruka and Juri</a>, but they make it look <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squee" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squee">adorable</a>. That is, if you forget about the, er... <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YM